{"questionId":"22509009","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Taylor intends to play the game for one hour.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Use the central limit theorem to find the probability that Taylor’s mean score per minute is greater than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>distribution of mean score is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>95</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mn>60</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>58833</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(A1)(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for normal distribution with mean <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, and <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for variance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>95</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mn>60</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mover><mi>T</mi><mo>¯</mo></mover><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>25</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>238</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>237576</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A2</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[4 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22509009","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ1.6d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-inte